{# templates/report.md.j2 — gate-operator overview.

   Renders a single ``_REPORT.md`` into the replica root. The
   summary extractor's output goes in verbatim; everything else
   gets a one-line per-kind tally with names listed inline.

   Inputs:
     basename       — source basename
     topic          — classify topic string
     quintet        — classify quintet object
     summary        — extract-summary's text (verbatim)

     artifact_extractions  — {kind: {materialised: [items], skipped: [items]}}
                             one entry per artifact-mode kind. ``materialised``
                             items got vault pages; ``skipped`` were extracted
                             but pruned (or never built) — informational only.
     synthesis_extractions — {kind: [items]} for synthesis-mode kinds (topics,
                             themes, etc.). These never become atomic pages;
                             they feed into the synthesis hub.

     synthesis_paths       — list of ``21 SYNTHESIS/<slug>.md`` paths written
                             by the synthesis agent.
     orphan_links          — list of wikilink targets in synthesis hubs that
                             match neither a surviving artifact nor an existing
                             vault page (broken links the operator may want to
                             fix before applying).

     manifest_modifications  — [{vault_path, kind, name}] for artifact pages
                               that overwrite an existing vault page (manifest
                               entries with op=modified).
     synthesis_modifications — [{vault_path, name}] for synthesis pages whose
                               path already exists in the vault and would be
                               overwritten.
#}
